commit.message: Fix type mismatch in printf() on 32-bit systems

Update GitHub Actions CI

Use latest Ubuntu image.
Fix missing man/sndfile-waveform.1 in tarball when using Autotools
Expand the man pages for sndfile-{generate-chirp,jackplay,mix-to-mono,spectrogram} to be at least as useful as their --help output
Adjust whitespace to pacify Scripts/cstyle.py
Replace remaining uses of memset() for structure initialization with C99 designated initializers

Fix #76, in which Valgrind reports a leaked FontConfig object in sndfile-spectrogram

Certain FontConfig objects indirectly referenced via the Cairo static
data are referenced by integer offsets rather than by pointers, so they
appear lost to Valgrind unless we call cairo_debug_reset_static_data().
Remove memset()s made redundant by C99-style zero-initializations added in 3d91cc9abea5745d9814e501a8a5b3cba3497f70
Fix a leaked cairo context in render_to_surface() in waveform.c
Zero-initialize SF_INFO structures everywhere else, too
Zero-initialize sfinfo in resample.c to fix Valgrind error “Conditional jump or move depends on uninitialised value(s)”
Release 1.5
